#[navbar]

#[section, $md:
    @../ (Documentation) / Casts

    # Casts

    Casts are explicit and target-driven. The receiving type says where the value is going. `cast`, `cast!` or `catch` says how conversion failure is handled.

    This keeps conversion local. You can see the source, target and failure path without asking the compiler to guess from distant code.
]

